title: Timing and Replay Anomalies
id: xxxxxxxx-xxxx-4xxx-yxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx #Der x er hex (0–9, a–f), og y er 8, 9, a eller b.
description: Detects timing-related anomalies in IEC-104 communication, including
  replayed ASDUs, decreasing or irregular sequence numbers, extremely low
  inter-packet timing (ΔT), or abnormally high ASDU rate from an RTU. Often found
  in replay attacks or Man-in-The-Middle attacks.
status: test
author: sigurdog
# date: xxxx/xx/xx

logsource:
  product: network
  service: ids

  # (1) Sequence number decreased (should be monotonic)
detection:
  seq_decrease:
    iec104.seq.anomaly: "decrease"     # supported by some ICS parsers
                                       # alternativ: see below fallback

  # (2) Small ΔT
  fast_replay:
    iec104.delta_ms|int: "<5"          # repeated frames too fast
    iec104.repeated_asdu: true         # requires IDS dedupe field

  # (3) More than X ASDUs per second from RTU
  high_rate:
    source_ip|in:
      - "10.20.0.133" # SCADA slave (RTU)
    event_rate: ">50/s"                # depends on backend (Elastic/Splunk)

  condition: seq_decrease or fast_replay or high_rate

fields:
  - source_ip
  - destination_ip
  - iec104.seq
  - iec104.delta_ms

falsepositives:
  - Clock drift in virtualized ICS testbeds
  - Burst traffic during RTU cold start

level: high

tags:
  -